      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THINK POSITIVE (1) had to overcome a collision with another runner and could manage only a distant fourth (28.04) in a Grade 5 over 488m at Mandurah. Has the ability and can bounce back. AEROPLANE BERNIE (8) missed the frame last time but had been racing well prior to that, winning a Grade 5 three back before a placing at Launceston the following run. Can turn it around this time. CANYA CELESTE (6) finished in the money two on end before breaking through for an overdue win last start (27.72) at Mandurah. Has never missed the frame here from four starts. Has a good overall strike-rate and can find the frame here. NAUGHTY EVIE (2) can run a bold race on best form.",
